ISSUED AT 0600 SATURDAY 30 JANUARY 2016
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0300: A STRONG TO GALE FORCE WESTERLY FLOW
COVERS IRELAND. EMBEDDED SHOWERY TROUGHS ARE MOVING EASTWARDS ACROSS THE
AREA. THE FLOW WILL MODERATE LATER TODAY AND A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
WILL DEVELOP OVERNIGHT.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM SLYNE HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD AND
FOR THE IRISH SEA NORTH OF ANGLESEY:
WIND: WEST TO SOUTHWEST FORCE 7 OR GALE FORCE 8 AND GUSTY BUT STRONG GALE
FORCE 9 BETWEEN SLYNE HEAD AND FAIR HEAD AT FIRST. WINDS DECREASING FORCE
5 TO 7 AND GUSTY LATER THIS AFTERNOON AND FURTHER MODERATING SOUTHWEST FORCE
4 OR 5 LATER TONIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM HOWTH HEAD TO HOOK HEAD TO SLYNE HEAD AND FOR
THE IRISH SEA SOUTH OF ANGLESEY:
WIND: WESTERLY FORCE 6 OR 7 AND GUSTY POSSIBLY TOUCHING GALE FORCE 8 ON
THE SOUTH IRISH SEA AT FIRST. WINDS DECREASING FORCE 5 OR 6 AND GUSTY THIS
AFTERNOON AND FURTHER MODERATING SOUTHWEST FORCE 4 OR 5 THIS EVENING. WINDS
WILL BACK SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST LATER TONIGHT.
WEATHER FOR ALL SEA AREAS: OCCASIONAL HEAVY SHOWERS. MOST FREQUENT IN THE
NORTH AND WEST SOME WINTRY AND WITH A RISK OF THUNDER. RAIN ON THE SOUTH
AND WEST COASTS LATER TONIGHT.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: ON SOUTHWEST WEST AND NORTHWEST COASTS.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 MONDAY 1 FEBRUARY 2016: FRESH
TO STRONG AND GUSTY SOUTHWEST WINDS ON THE SOUTH AND WEST COASTS DURING SUNDAY
MORNING WILL EXTEND TO REMAIN NG COASTS AND THE IRISH SEA AFTER DARK AND
WILL INCREASE GALE TO STRONG GALE FORCE AND GUSTY OVERT IG IT OCCASIONAL
SHOWERS AT FIRST SOME WINTRY AND WITH THUNDER. RAIN WILL SPREAD FROM THE
SOUTH AND SOUTHWEST DURING SUNDAY.
WARNING OF HEAVY ATLANTIC SWELL: ON SOUTHWEST WEST AND NORTHWEST COASTS.
TEXT OF GALE WARNING
WESTERLY GALES OR STRONG GALES TODAY ON IRISH COASTAL WATERS FROM SLYNE
HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD AND ON THE IRISH SEA NORTH OF ANGLESEY.
TEXT OF SMALL CRAFT WARNING
SOUTHWEST TO WEST WINDS WILL REACH FORCE 6 OR HIGHER THIS MORNING ON COASTS
FROM HOWTH HEAD TO HOOK HEAD TO SLYNE HEAD.
